- [x] dont drop health packs if the player is at 100%, drop ammo or armor instead — `rollLoot()` (`loot.ts`) gained a `playerAtFullHealth` flag that filters `"health"` out of the weight table entirely (same pattern as the existing `hasRocketLauncher` filter for `"rockets"`), redistributing its share across bullets/rockets/swap instead of re-rolling into it; the regular-kill call site in `engine.ts` now passes `this.health >= MAX_HEALTH`. Elite kills bypass that table with their own guaranteed-health branch, so `dropEliteLoot` gained a matching full-health check that falls back to a new elite-sized bullets/swap drop (`ELITE_BULLETS_DROP_AMOUNT`/`ELITE_SWAP_DROP_AMOUNT`) instead of the guaranteed `ELITE_HEALTH_DROP_AMOUNT` pack. Verified against the real `RaycasterEngine` in headless Chromium: 400 trials of a regular kill at full health never rolled `"health"` (still rolled ammo/swap), 400 trials below full health still could, 400 trials of an elite kill at full health (weapons pre-owned to force past the weapon-drop branch) never rolled `"health"` and consistently fell back to bullets/swap, and an elite kill below full health still guaranteed its health pack unchanged [Task 50]
